The Chinese mainland recorded 37 confirmed COVID-19 cases on Monday, with 9 linked to local transmissions and 28 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Tuesday. A total of 105 asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Monday, and 1,449 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. The cumulative number of confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland is 225,318, with the death toll from COVID-19 standing at 5,226. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 334,996 (63,253 recoveries, 9,396 deaths) Macao: 93 (83 recoveries) Taiwan: 3,330,695 (13,742 recoveries, 5,365 deaths)